SA's World Cup winning Springbok captain Siya Kolisi received a rapturous reception at OR Tambo International Airport in Johannesburg on Tuesday. The airport was a sea of green and gold as rugby fans welcomed their captain and coach Rassie Erasmus back from Japan. Vice-captain Handre Pollard was also among the players who arrived at the airport on Tuesday evening. Kolisi and Erasmus addressed the media during a briefing. Watch the proceedings here.